metadata.name: Triangular Dreams #26
metadata.description:
Delaunay triangulation is a good old resource in the generative toolbox. In this work I’ve tried to give it a new twist, combining it with different methods to place points in space, and filling each triangle with lines that go from one corner to the opposite side. The goal is to generate a wide range of semi-abstract scenes, that can sometimes be reminiscent of the work of Paul Klee, Lyonel Feininger or other Bauhaus members.

Controls:
[c] to switch between 3 color modes: color mixes, color zones and monochrome
[f] to toggle fullscreen
[s] to save a screen capture
[2] to [9] to generate and save a hi-res image at 2x, 3x, … your viewport size

This work will adapt nicely to any screen format.
No palettes have been used, it is all random colors within a certain hue and saturation range.
Made with p5.js and d3.js

metadata.name: Self, Superego #131
metadata.description:
The second installment of the Self trilogy.

Superego is defined as: the one of the three divisions of the psyche in psychoanalytic theory that is only partly conscious, represents internalization of parental conscience and the rules of society, and functions to reward and punish through a system of moral attitudes, conscience, and a sense of guilt.

Please see attached fx(text) article or go to https://ty-vek.art/self-trilogy for more on concept/mechanics/etc. It’s a bit of long read, but worth it.

—————————

All projects are written in vanilla Javascript, composed as SVG and then rendered to a 2d canvas.

There might be slight differences in rendering from browser to browser. This is expected as they might translate the SVG slightly differently. Let's call Chromium renderings canonical. They also render faster there and we love that.

Press "S" to save a PNG.
Press "V" to save a SVG. (Chromium browsers render these pretty well.)

By default, these will render at 2400 x 3200 pixels. This is at density 1.

To render at a larger resolution you can append “&d=2” to the end of the url. This will double the resolution. You can also use 3 or 4 or whatever your browser can handle. Safari tends to have problems with this, so stick with Chromium based browsers (Chrome, Edge, Brave, etc.)

If you want to render as a square image, so it is optimized for ummm.. your pfp or something, you can append “&sq=t” to the url.

If you want to get rid of grain, just append “&g=n”

—————————

https://twitter.com/ty__vek
https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/Ty%20Vek/articles

metadata.name: the Glory of Colours #83
metadata.description:
According to Kandinsky, painting “can create the same energies in the observer that music can make in the listener. The abstract painter is an echo seeker: just like the relationship between music and the listener, shapes and colors must penetrate the observer's soul. They vibrate the threads of his existence and resonate in the depths of his mind, you can still find references to people, buildings, mountains, etc., but these are more signs than manifestations. They do not evoke objects but abstractly reveal them, like the simplified image we have seen before of objects and elements in nature.
Classical philosophy reinforces the belief that existing, tangible reality is a mask for a deeper reality that can only be reached through imagination. I have tried to combine this with the art of coding and creating canvases of millions of characters and numbers.
Made in p5js
Created July 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: MoodColors #52
metadata.description: The artwork is based on principles of Orphism and Bauhaus , as one of the most striking examples of a combination of functionality, simplicity and at the same time the ability to convey the underlying meaning, where the form is determined by function. Where color is one of the most important values. Our goal is to visualize all the richness and versatility of human emotions with the help of color. What, if not color, is able to convey the whole gamut of feelings and experiences that we experience.  Every bright event in our life, both positive and negative, always leaves its mark in our memory. We show it through lines – it's like wrinkles on the face, marks of the experience, like a note on a sheet, a dash / tick, like an entry in the diary of life, where the sheet on which we made a note is colored in the color of emotions and sensations that we experienced again and again. It's always a lot of mixed shades that have their own unique palette.  The fundamental emotions and feelings such as anger, sadness, fear, disgust, joy and love are taken. Each token is one emotion, where with the help of color we show how multifaceted it can be.

metadata.name: Abstract Life #66
metadata.description:
The concept of organic, obtained from living systems, is said to be an effect that, like a plant and a living being, has grown in a completely dynamic manner in different degrees, and no factor except vital forces has prevented its growth. Organic creation is an example of this type. Léonard de Vinci believed in nature; he wrote, "Painting is a child of nature" in his opinion, art should be compatible with nature. His public image of creativity was "innovation while maintaining fidelity" to nature. According to Michelangelo, the form the artist gives to the materials is in the artist's mind and the materials themselves. Therefore, the artist is always in a metaphysical struggle with the form and secrets of nature. This is a revelatory process through which the artist discovers the mass of paper already hidden in his mind and the materials. As an architect, I tried to create this work while paying attention to the structuralism of shapes and forms in creation, inspired by the colors in nature and my experience in painting and illustration.

To spread the vibe of my beautiful community, minters will own 50% of royalty on each secondary sale.
Eighteen different color palettes and three different borders are used in this artwork.
Made in p5js
Created August 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: Inland Emotions #152
metadata.description:
Inland Emotions

Over the centuries, ancient philosophers and modern psychologists have come to the same basic conclusion. The fact is that, according to a few millennia of research, there are a limited number of distinct human emotions, predefined by the human psyche. Sometimes it may seem like we are experiencing a "new" one, but on closer inspection, we see that it is the known emotions that are superimposed. Emotions are what they are, and they exist in the same way in each of us, whether we recognize them for what they are or not. But as our history blends into a new emerging state of the world, a whole new range of emotional responses are triggered within us. An infinite maelstrom of variations generated from a simple combination of a few emotions.


Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

Inland Emotions by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Wandering Nets Redux #21
metadata.description:
Wandering Nets Redux is a reissue of Wandering Nets (March 2022). Due to an unfortunate error in the original piece Wandering Nets no longer displays live inside the current fxhash UI. This restored and updated generative token is offered free to all collectors of the original, with some additional tweaks and capabilities.

January 2023

Original description as below:

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Wandering Nets is a digital kinetic light sculpture by Matt Ebb.

Networks of light are created and connected via random walks in space and colour. Emergent structures are revealed by the ambient interaction, tension and collision of these networks within themselves and orbiting shadowed spherical bodies.

The piece is the result of several months of custom development in realtime volume rendering. The scene data is generated in javascript and rendered with a bespoke GLSL raytracer - no external libraries are used.

This is a graphically intensive shader. By default it will adaptively adjust sampling quality to target 30fps, though a reasonably fast GPU is recommended for best results.

Mouse drag: Orbit the camera in 3D to explore compositions
[ and ] keys: Override the adaptive samples per pixel lower or higher to trade noise for framerate

March 2022

Update -
spacebar: Disturb the light positions

metadata.name: fx_dungeon(plans) #3
metadata.description:
This is just a random level generator from fx_dungeon. It designs a complete level map, without player, coins to collect or controls. 

It can be used for fun, or even to generate dungeons for your homebrew TTRPGs. I'm leaving the exploration open anyways.

## Controls
- Move the player around using WASD or the arrow keys. Interact with stairs using SPACEBAR or E
- You can click the image to toggle sound on or off

## Credits
- I'm using p5js and I also tweaked to my needs a tutorial from Daniel Schiffman about raycasting
